s to expedite and streamline cancer genomics research to guide cancer treatment ultimately our vision is to fully deliver on the promise of precision oncology and to create better treatment options for all people with cancer thanks to our powerful combination of clinical and scientific resources focused exclusively on cancer memorial sloan kettering is in a unique position to reach this ambitious goal the mariejosée and henry r kravis center for molecular oncology spans the full range of activities required to translate molecular insights into clinical innovations — from procuring and archiving patient tissues to pioneering the latest diagnostic tests and targeted therapies related topics how basket trials are transforming oncology the mariejosée and henry r kravis center for molecular oncology aims to transform genomic medicine and cancer care reaching a milestone researchers report results of first  patients analyzed by mskimpact aacr basket trial for experimental drug shows promising early results with msk leading the way precision medicine links lab research to patient care innovative research center will explore hereditary cancer genes a computational biologist explains how cancer patient data leads to personalized medicine media coverage why doctors are trying a skin cancer drug to treat a brain tumor what are exceptional responders expanding the impact of precision medicine to fuel discoveries beyond the usual suspects study of noncoding dna reveals new mutations linked to cancer a sneak preview of our annual “major trends” seminar live webcast landmark  million gift from the mariejosée and henry r kravis foundation supports a groundbreaking approach to precision oncology tumor sequencing test brings personalized treatment options to more patients media coverage cancer ‘miracle’ patients studied anew for disease clues genetic testing of lung tumors leads to better therapies bold initiative to transform cancer care established with a  million gift at work physicianscientist david solit landmark gift of  million from the mariejosée and henry r kravis foundation will support groundbreaking approach to precision oncology henry r kravis  wealthx already logged in proceed to sign in here products  servicesindustriesintelligence centreallwealthx reportswealthx insightsdaily newsaboutcontactfollow us client login wealthx billionaires henry r kravis henry r kravis primary position cochairman primary company kkr  company estimated net worth at least  billion source of wealth selfmade age  birthday  january  religion jewish nationality united states hometown tulsa oklahoma united states marital status married biography kravis received his bachelors degree in economics from claremont mckenna college in  and interned with money management firm madison fund he went on to obtain his mba from columbia university in  served as vice president of katy industries a new yorkbased stock exchange company and was responsible for designing and implementing acquisition programs kravis then joined bear stearns where his cousin george roberts and jerome kohlberg were working and served as a partner until  in  kravis cofounded kkr  co  contact us to see more biography education history institution name eaglebrook school qualification name diploma education type primary school start date   end date  contact us to see more education history interesting facts kkr  co owns a  challenger  business jet purchased in  serial number  registration number ntf expired in january   a  bombardier global express jet purchased in  serial number  registration number new expires in march   and a  hawker xp purchased in  serial number  registration number nam expired in january   the jets are owned through eac air ewa west and abme aviation respectively contact us to see more interesting facts interests passion hobbies kind of interests passion and hobbies health and wellness description kravis and his wife mariejosee reportedly donated  million to new yorkbased canc