cular health as well as funding a professorship they have also endowed the chair in human oncology at memorial sloankettering cancer center in new york he previously cochaired with jerry speyer the influential partnership for new york city founded by david rockefeller in  and now sits on its board of directors he created the new york city investment fund a nonprofit organization to create jobs and new business in new york city he is a trustee of the council on foreign relations in new york chairman of sponsors for educational opportunity and is a member of the executive committee of the business council for    and  he cochairs the columbia business school board of overseers where he recently pledged a gift of  million to support the schools new campus project and is a vicechairman of rockefeller university see alsoedit kohlberg kravis roberts list of claremont mckenna college people history of private equity and venture capital private equity leveraged buyout rjr nabisco referencesedit  a b c forbes the worlds billionaires  henry kravis september   jerusalem post the worlds  richest jews    henry kravis september    profile achievementorg accessed september    httpwwwanswerscomtopickohlbergkravisrobertsco answerscom profile  in  kravis was forced to serve as interim ceo of a failing direct mail company advo  refers to henry hillman and the hillman company the hillman company answerscom profile  burrough bryan barbarians at the gate new york harper  row  pp   the biggest deal ever demott deborah a duke law journal  no  lonkevich dan and klump edward kkr texas pacific will acquire txu for  billion bloomberg february    dodson steve beatrice deal is biggest buyout yet the new york times november    fisher lawrence m safeway buyout a success story the new york times october    sorkin andrew ross and rozhon tracie three firms are said to buy toys r us for  billion new york times march    kkr offer of  billion is accepted by first data reuters april    myerson allen r and